alternatives.transcript: presenting to you today a sixty two year old female patient leslie palmer who showed up today to the er with chief complaints of fatigue shortness of breath and palpitations that started two months ago which has been getting worse patient stated to have visited her family medicine provider three days ago but since then her symptoms have gotten haven't gotten any better and i would classify her as a n nyha classification of three patients say that she had fatigue and gained eight pounds since the start of her symptoms patient also stated that she had wheezing orthopnea and dyspnea with exertion for her cardiovascular symptoms she stated that she had palpitations presyncope but no chest pain her musculoskeletal symptoms were all negative except for swelling in her lower extremities otherwise everything was else was insignificant for her her ros the patient has hypertension and pulmonary sarcoidosis that was diagnosed twenty five years ago the patient had a cardiac cath done a year ago with no significant results otherwise no other hospitalizations patient has no known allergies she stated that she had a balanced diet used to walk every day with friends but was unable to nowadays due to her symptoms she's not taking any illicit drugs no no tobacco or alcohol she drinks a cup of coffee every day and is an elementary school teacher she's also married and has someone to take care of her throughout her medical care and she has insurance her patient died suddenly at the age of forty and her father died of a heart attack at the age of fifty nine for her physical exam i noted a positive jugular venous distension but no carotid bruise no rashes no petechiae no purpura she had bibasilar reals and wheezing point of maximum impulse was normal with no chest wall tenderness she had a positive one pitting lower extremity edema and had a full and equal posterior tibial pulses her calf was nontender her heart was regular with a systolic murmur of s four no pericardial friction rub but positive for gallops she had a heart rate of a hundred and ten respiratory rate of twenty blood pressure of one thirty six over ninety nine pulse was one zero eight and her temperature was ninety eight point six degrees fahrenheit for her lab she only had elevated bnp levels chest x-ray showed infiltration in her lungs a widened mediastinum and a normal sized heart the echo resulted results showed restrictive cardiomyopathy with an ejection fraction of fifty five percent her ekg showed normal sinus and access with a nonsustained ventricular tachycardia so patient the patient was diagnosed with sarcoidosis restrictive cardiomyopathy and she'll be admitted to the hospital patient will be continuing her lisinopril ten milligrams i increased her prednisone to sixty milligrams and then i added an amiodarone one fifty milligrams iv and furosemide forty milligrams iv i'll be ordering cnp labs for her and i will also be consulting consulting interventional cardiology for an i aicd placement and radiology for a feg pet scan patient will also be given oxygen via the nasal cannula to maintain her oxygen saturation above ninety six percent and i counseled the patient on maintaining a low sodium diet and not getting out of bed without assistance thank you
